properties.description:
This is a series of performances for the benefit of the Arlington Planetarium sponsored by the Sonic Circuits Festival of Experimental Music (<a href="http://www.dc-soniccircuits.org/">http://www.dc-soniccircuits.org/</a>).  The Arlington County School Board has proposed closing the Planetarium unless significant funds can be raised  for upgrades and continued operations. The Planetarium is a resource for science education in Arlington County and has provided services for over forty years to students and the greater Arlington community.
A diverse group of DC-area musicians will be contributing their talents in a series of performances at the Planetarium on November 12, 13 and 14:
Bluebrain (<a href="http://www.bluebra.in/">http://www.bluebra.in/</a>)
 will perform Friday, November 12, beginning at 7 PM (doors open at 6:30);
Janel and Anthony (<a href="http://www.myspace.com/janelandanthony">http://www.myspace.com/janelandanthony</a>) will perform on Saturday, November 13, beginning at 3:30 PM (doors open at 3:00);
The Twenty-first Century Chamber Ensemble (<a href="http://www.myspace.com/xxichamberensemblepartone">http://www.myspace.com/xxichamberensemblepartone</a>), together with Doug Kallmeyer (<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/302_Acid">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/302_Acid</a>), will perform on Saturday, November 13, beginning at 6:00 PM (doors open at 5:30);
The Lost Civilizations experimental music project (<a href="http://www.myspace.com/lostcivilizationsmusic">http://www.myspace.com/lostcivilizationsmusic</a>), together with Doug Kallmeyer,  will perform on Sunday, November 14, at 3:30 (doors open at 3:00) and 6:00 PM (doors open at 5:30).
Seating (other than for advance ticket sales) will be on a first-come/first-served basis due to the Planetarium's limited seating.  Beginning November 12, tickets will be available at the Planetarium for performances in this weekend series.
